      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "IAN ALBERT (4) doesn't have the best strike-rate but recent form is sound. Continues to race well, filling the minors at the last three starts, the latest when second (30.19) at this track. Has a good record here at this journey. Goes well out of this box with a win and four minor placings. Likely to be in the finish again. WEBLEC MEMPHIS (7) missed the frame latest when fifth at Geelong (26.23) but was a winner four back in the second best time of the program. Returns to favourable track. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Will give the top chances plenty to think about. MOMENT (1) returned a better run last time, finishing in the money (30.13) at this track behind Crackerjack Hops in a Grade 5. Has the pace to be prominent. Bold showing expected. DR. BEYOND (5) missed the placings here most recently but can sneak into the finish with the right run.",
